{"timestamp": "2025-12-02 17:02:25.773146", "event": "llm_end", "text": "Diagnostic report — SDN spine–leaf lab\nSummary\n- Anomaly detected: Hosts on the 10.0.0.0/24 tenant subnet cannot reach each other. Inter-host pings fail with \"Destination Host Unreachable\".\n- Control/management plane (20.0.0.0/24) appears functional: switches can reach the controller (example: leaf_1 can ping 20.0.0.100).\n- Data-plane forwarding on the OVS bridges is not operating: the OVS bridge interfaces (the bridge device names, e.g., \"leaf_1\", \"leaf_2\", \"spine_1\") are administratively/down and OVS kernel datapath appears not to be providing L2 forwarding.\n- Localization: The problem is localized to the OVS dataplane on the switches (leaf_1, leaf_2 — and likely spine_1), not the hosts nor the controller connectivity.\n\nObserved behavior and evidence\n1) Host-to-host connectivity failure (10.0.0.0/24)\n- From host_1_1 -> host_1_2:\n  - ping output: \"From 10.0.0.1 icmp_seq=1 Destination Host Unreachable\" (100% loss).\n- From host_1_1 -> host_2_1:\n  - ping output: same \"Destination Host Unreachable\".\n- From host_1_2 -> host_1_1:\n  - ping output: \"From 10.0.0.2 icmp_seq=1 Destination Host Unreachable\".\n- Interpretation: the source hosts cannot deliver frames to the target; the kernel is reporting host unreachable (indicating no forwarding/ARP resolution at L2 inside the switch/bridge).\n\n2) OVS bridge and service state on leaf switches\n- leaf_1:\n  - ifconfig/ip addr: internal bridge interface \"leaf_1\" shows flags=4098 (no UP) — the bridge device is DOWN; eth0..eth3 are present and UP but the bridge itself is not UP. eth6 (management) is UP with 20.0.0.3.\n  - systemctl status openvswitch-switch: \"Active: inactive (dead)\" (service unit not active).\n  - However ovsdb-server and ovs-vswitchd processes are present (ps shows ovsdb-server and ovs-vswitchd running).\n  - ovs-vsctl show: Bridge leaf_1 exists, controller tcp:20.0.0.100:6633 configured, fail_mode secure.\n  - leaf_1 can ping controller: successful (0% loss).\n- leaf_2:\n  - same pattern: bridge device \"leaf_2\" interface is DOWN (not up), eth6 has management 20.0.0.4 and is functional.\n  - systemctl openvswitch-switch: inactive (dead) while ovsdb-server/ovs-vswitchd processes are present.\n  - ovs-vsctl show shows Bridge leaf_2 with controller configured.\n- spine_1:\n  - the bridge device \"spine_1\" is also shown as present but its bridge interface is in DOWN state (ifconfig lists \"spine_1: flags=4098\" — not UP). eth4 has 20.0.0.1 (management) and is UP.\n\n3) Management/control plane OK\n- leaf_1 ping to controller (20.0.0.100) works:\n  - \"3 packets transmitted, 3 received, 0% packet loss, rtt avg 0.799 ms\".\n- ovs-vsctl shows controllers set to tcp:20.0.0.100:6633 on the leaf bridges.\n\nLocalization (faulty components)\n- Primary devices implicated:\n  - leaf_1 (OVS bridge internal device DOWN, openvswitch-switch service inactive despite ovs daemons running).\n  - leaf_2 (same symptoms).\n  - spine_1 shows the bridge device DOWN as well and should be considered potentially affected.\n- Affected functions:\n  - Software switching datapath / L2 forwarding on the OVS bridges connecting hosts in 10.0.0.0/24.\n- Not implicated:\n  - Hosts' IP configuration on 10.0.0.0/24: hosts have correct 10.0.0.x addresses and interfaces are up.\n  - Management network (20.0.0.0/24) and controller reachability: working.\n\nLikely root cause(s) (reasoned)\n- Core issue: the OVS datapath/bridge interfaces are not active (bridge devices are DOWN / ovs-system appears DOWN), so the switches are not forwarding tenant-subnet L2 traffic.\n- Contributing observations that support this root cause:\n  - Bridge device (named after the switch) is present but its interface is not UP (ifconfig shows the bridge with flags without UP/LOWER_UP).\n  - The kernel datapath interface \"ovs-system\" is in state DOWN on the leaf hosts — that suggests the kernel datapath is not fully operational for user-level OVS to present L2 forwarding.\n  - systemctl reports openvswitch-switch service inactive (dead) on leaf_1 and leaf_2 while ovsdb-server and ovs-vswitchd processes are running. That discrepancy suggests a service lifecycle or init issue (service unit may not be running correctly to manage the datapath), or the userspace daemons were started outside of systemd and the kernel datapath module (or datapath setup) was not completed/initialized.\n  - Because the management plane is reachable and controllers are configured, the control plane (OpenFlow channel) is not the immediate cause — the problem is at the local datapath/bridge level on the switches.\n\nImpact\n- No L2 connectivity between hosts on 10.0.0.0/24. All intra-subnet host-to-host traffic is failing.\n- Controller and switch management communications (20.0.0.0/24) are functional — monitoring and control plane alive, but data-plane switching is broken.\n\nRelevant outputs (excerpted)\n- host ping: \"From 10.0.0.1 icmp_seq=1 Destination Host Unreachable\" (host_1_1 -> host_1_2).\n- leaf_1 systemctl: \"openvswitch-switch.service ... Active: inactive (dead)\".\n- leaf_1 processes: ovsdb-server and ovs-vswitchd present (ps output).\n- leaf_1 ifconfig/ip addr: bridge \"leaf_1\" is DOWN; eth6 shows inet 20.0.0.3/24.\n- ovs-vsctl show (leaf_1): Bridge leaf_1 exists; Controller \"tcp:20.0.0.100:6633\"; fail_mode secure.\n- leaf_1 -> controller ping: \"3 packets transmitted, 3 received, 0% packet loss\".\n\nAdditional diagnostic notes / suggested checks (for confirmation only)\n- Inspect kernel modules and datapath state (e.g., check dmesg for openvswitch, check for openvswitch kernel module loaded).\n- Check system logs for openvswitch-switch service unit (journalctl -u openvswitch-switch) to see why systemd thinks the service is inactive.\n- Inspect ovs-vswitchd logs (/var/log/openvswitch/ovs-vswitchd.log) and ovsdb-server logs for datapath initialization errors.\n- Check link/port status and if the internal bridge device is administratively down (ip link show leaf_1).\n- Confirm whether ovsdb/vswitchd are managing the kernel datapath or running in userspace-only mode.\n\nConclusion\n- The network exhibits a clear data-plane failure: OVS bridge devices on the switches are not active and are not forwarding tenant-subnet traffic, while management/control plane remains reachable. The most likely root cause is a problem in OVS datapath initialization on the switches (bridge interfaces are down and openvswitch service reporting inactive), preventing L2 forwarding between host-facing ports on leaf switches (and likely affecting spine).", "generation_info": {"finish_reason": "stop", "logprobs": null}, "invalid_tool_calls": [], "usage_metadata": {"input_tokens": 31131, "output_tokens": 3589, "total_tokens": 34720, "input_token_details": {"audio": 0, "cache_read": 30720}, "output_token_details": {"audio": 0, "reasoning": 1920}}}
